"title": "8820: self-confidence",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8820: self-confidence",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A positive assessment of one's own abilities and resources. Scripture censures excessive self-confidence, in that such an attitude lacks humility and fails to recognise the role of God's grace in the Christian life.</p>\n<h2>Excessive self-confidence</h2>\n<h3>In one's own abilities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:15\">ISA 28:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:33-Matt26:35\">MAT 26:33–26:35</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:29-Mark14:31\">MRK 14:29–14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:33-Luke23:34\">LUK 23:33–23:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:37-John13:38\">JHN 13:37–13:38</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:33-Luke22:34\">LUK 22:33–22:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:20\">JDG 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:11\">1KI 20:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:23-2Kgs19:24\">2KI 19:23–19:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:13-Job8:14\">JOB 8:13–8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:5-Ps49:6\">PSA 49:5–49:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:5\">JER 17:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:8\">HOS 12:8</a></p>\n<h3>Excessive self-confidence leads to pride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:9-Isa9:10\">ISA 9:9–9:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:3\">OBA 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:4\">GEN 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:5\">GEN 37:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:9\">EXO 15:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16\">2CH 26:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:18\">PRO 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:6\">ISA 16:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:2\">EZK 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:9\">ACT 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:17-Rom11:18\">ROM 11:17–11:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:2\">1CO 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Challenges to excessive self-confidence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:16\">NEH 6:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:7\">1CO 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:12-Ps49:13\">PSA 49:12–49:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:7\">PSA 52:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:5-Prov3:7\">PRO 3:5–3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:28\">PRO 11:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:26\">PRO 28:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:21\">ISA 5:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:13-Isa14:15\">ISA 14:13–14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:7\">JER 49:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:4-Jer49:5\">JER 49:4–49:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:13-Jas4:16\">JAS 4:13–4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Excessive self-confidence is a barrier to justification</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>\n<h2>Accurate self-confidence</h2>\n<h3>Of one's natural advantages</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:4-Phil3:6\">PHP 3:4–3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:3\">ACT 22:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:28\">ACT 22:28</a></p>\n<h3>Of one's experience of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:2\">2CO 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:4-Acts22:21\">ACT 22:4–22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:1\">2CO 12:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:5-2Cor13:6\">2CO 13:5–13:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:13-Gal1:17\">GAL 1:13–1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:4\">GAL 6:4</a></p>\n<h3>Of one's calling to serve</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:8\">2CO 10:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:13-2Cor10:17\">2CO 10:13–10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:7\">GAL 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Of one's service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:19\">ACT 20:19</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:3\">ROM 12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:18\">ACT 20:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:20-Acts20:21\">ACT 20:20–20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:15-1Cor9:18\">1CO 9:15–9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:12\">2CO 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:16\">PHP 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:1-1Thess2:12\">1TH 2:1–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Of one's own weakness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:29-2Cor11:30\">2CO 11:29–11:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:21-2Cor11:28\">2CO 11:21–11:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:9</a></p>\n<h3>Accurate self-estimates lead to justification</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>\n<h3>Justified self-confidence may appear as pride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:17-2Cor11:18\">2CO 11:17–11:18</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's accurate assessment of himself</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:15-Matt16:17\">MAT 16:15–16:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:29\">MRK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:20-Luke9:21\">LUK 9:20–9:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:62-Matt26:64\">MAT 26:62–26:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:13\">JHN 13:13</a></p>\n<h2>The proper source of all confidence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:23-Jer9:24\">JER 9:23–9:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:2\">PSA 34:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:6-Ps44:7\">PSA 44:6–44:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:15\">ISA 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:27-1Cor1:31\">1CO 1:27–1:31</a></p>",
